        "pull_request": {
          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tnshgarg/sentinel-ops/pulls/1",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/tnshgarg/sentinel-ops/pull/1",
          "diff_url": "https://github.com/tnshgarg/sentinel-ops/pull/1.diff",
          "patch_url": "https://github.com/tnshgarg/sentinel-ops/pull/1.patch",
          "merged_at": "2026-04-01T16:40:23Z"
        },
        "body": "Bugs fixed\r\nRemoved dead inspected_anomaly variable that was computed and then immediately overwritten, never used. Clean logic now.\r\n\r\nSession management \r\nReplaced single global _env with _sessions: Dict[str, SentinelOpsEnvironment]\r\nAdded optional session_id field to ResetRequest and StepRequest — omitting it defaults to \"default\" for full backward compatibility\r\nAll endpoints (/reset, /step, /state, /grade) are now session-aware and return session_id in responses\r\nConcurrent grader calls no longer corrupt each other's state\r\n\r\n\r\nTracks every completed /grade call in memory\r\nReturns aggregate stats: total episodes, average score, best/worst score, per-difficulty breakdown with efficiency ratio (optimal_steps / actual_steps)\r\n\r\n\r\nENABLE_VISION now defaults to \"true\" — the agent actually sees camera frames, which is the entire point of a visual surveillance benchmark\r\n\r\nAdded 7 explicit DECISION RULES that force the agent to be decisive: classify risk immediately after finding an anomaly, escalate/dismiss on the very next action, never repeat the same action twice\r\n\r\nDetects when the agent repeats the same action 3 times consecutively\r\nInjects a hard stop prompt forcing classify_risk → escalate/dismiss, preventing step exhaustion and truncation penalties\r\n6 new tasks (12 total, up from 6)",
